@chapter First Start

Upon first start of the UI (@code{bashstyle} executable) the user will be
presented with a notice that a startup entry for @b{BashStyle-NG} has to be
added to ~/.bashrc in order for @b{BashStyle-NG} to actually work.

The user can either let the application add the entry on it's own or follow the
instruction to do it manually. To manually enable @b{BashStyle-NG}, add

@code{[[ -f /usr/share/bashstyle-ng/rc/bashstyle-rc ]] && source /usr/share/bashstyle-ng/rc/bashstyle-rc}

to your @code{~/.bashrc}.

